8 years later... I am still detoxing. # sober # soberlife

I was 4 - 6 attempts to quit. Then I was the pagan who wouldn’t go to AA. The one in the magickal circle who intended to be free of addiction. I kept trying. with community. 100 of us. together is the way. find your “together.” forgive yourself. keep trying. # sober # soberlife

I was that friend that passed out and lost clothes at every party. every. time. I was the accident waiting to happen at 115 mph. I was the dancer that couldn’t see straight and drank more than they made. I was organs waiting to fail. # sober # soberlife

This summer, most summers, I crave more intimacy. This looks like me going to more circles, dances, meditations, and other mostly dry events. Places where people merge without alcohol. (11th/12th house in Cancer.) # sober # soberlife

Both drinks were with Cancers who like to drink w/company. I don’t know enough about astrology to speculate on this coincidence but I know to watch fun-loving water signs with ideas about what I should be doing. # sober # soberlife

Today is the 8-year anniversary of my last drink. I was at a showing of Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince. It was a Guinness Shake. It was gross. <3’d Guinness but waited to late maybe. The drink before that was at New Year's. Also gross. Neither worth it. # sober # soberlife
